es and by generating a plethora of images in their homes. Gerritsen argues that these images are a crucial part of the everyday affective modes of engagement with family members and film stars but they are also symbolizing the political realm in which fans situate themselves. At the same time, Gerritsen shows how these image productions seem to concur with other visual regimes articulated in government restrictions, world class imaginaries and upper class moralities as presented on India's urban streets.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aFamilieszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aFans (Persons)zIndiazTamil NaduxPsychology. 0aMotion picture audienceszIndiazTamil NaduxPsychology. 0aMotion picture industryxSocial aspectszIndia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aFan and Audience Studies. 4aHistory of Film. 4aSouth Asia. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aAnthropology, South India, fandom, visual culture, urban space, affect.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048536269zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048536269423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048536269.jpg  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE A